page.title: 19Woodland north of Tregony
page.content: { Pomery Wood}(924463) is a coniferous wood and some of it is a plantation. The wood consists mainly of pine, fur and spruce. There are several tracks on its outer perimeter. Many of the trees have been cut down and as a result this wood is not very dense. It covers an area of 275 sq.m. {Golden Wood}(934464) is a broadleav- ed wood and has only a few conifers here and there. There are hardly any tracks. The wide variety of trees here includes oak, ash, poplar, willow and beech. This wood is far denser than Pomery Wood and covers 379 sq.m. {Carveth Wood}(925457) is also coniferous and is much like Golden Wood. However, it has fewer tree varieties; these include ash, beech and holly. There are no tracks in the wood which is very dense and covers an area of about 380 sq.m.
